Date:  0/0/1988
Source:  Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:  McGILL
Vol / Page:  51
Edition:
Quote:  go for the doctor again your supreme effort, or betting all your money on one race; the phrase comes from a card game called `forty-fives', popular on the West Coast from goldmining times, of Irish origin; author's  Ghost Towns of New Zealand: `Gambling was poker or 45s, a diggers' game ... involving legs, queer suits and Maggie, cries of `Get jinx!' and `Go for the doctor!'' NZA.
